<Algorithm code="           1. Let _ry_ be ℝ(_y_).           1. [declared=&#34;numYears1,numYears4,numYears100,numYears400&#34;] NOTE: In the following steps, _numYears1_, _numYears4_, _numYears100_, and _numYears400_ represent the number of years divisible by 1, 4, 100, and 400, respectively, that occur between the epoch and the start of year _y_. The number is negative if _y_ is before the epoch.           1. Let _numYears1_ be (_ry_ - 1970).           1. Let _numYears4_ be floor((_ry_ - 1969) / 4).           1. Let _numYears100_ be floor((_ry_ - 1901) / 100).           1. Let _numYears400_ be floor((_ry_ - 1601) / 400).           1. Return 𝔽(365 × _numYears1_ + _numYears4_ - _numYears100_ + _numYears400_).         ">
